scFlow - Cell-type and Cluster Overview Report

07 May, 2020

Dimensionality Reduction Plots

Cell-types

This two-dimensional embedding of cells should illustrate separation of cell-types into distinct clusters. An optimal plot should demonstrate separation between different cell-types; if not, it may be useful to manually re-annotate cell-types with reference to cell-type associated marker genes.

Figure: UMAP plot of cell-types. Each cell is coloured by annotated cell-type.

Clusters

Optimal clustering parameters should provide a level of granularity sufficient to identify minority cell-types as distinct numbered clusters. If any smaller clusters are encompassed by their adjacent cluster, the clustering parameters should be revised.

Figure: UMAP plot of clusters. Each cell is coloured by annotated cluster.
